# Push verification (before `pnpm push`)

When the user asks to **push**, **ship**, **`pnpm push`**, or you finish web changes intended for `main`:

**`pnpm push` only commits and pushes** — it does **not** run lint or build. You must run checks first.

## Required order (do not skip or reorder)

1. `npm run lint`
2. `npm run build` when changes touch `apps/web/src/app/**`, `apps/web/src/lib/**`, or `apps/web/src/types/**`; `npm run build:ops` when changes touch `apps/ops/**` or `packages/shared/**`
3. Targeted unit tests for touched logic, e.g. `node --import tsx --test apps/web/src/lib/<name>.test.ts`
4. `pnpm push`

## Prohibited

- Push without `npm run build` when routes, server lib, or shared types changed
- Use `npx tsx --test` (use `node --import tsx --test` instead)
- Run lint/build/test **in parallel** with each other
- Run an extra unrelated full-project lint **after** the push sequence already passed lint
- Use Multitask / background subagents for small tasks (roughly ≤5 files, single feature)

## Efficiency

- One linear pipeline: lint → build → test → push
- Do not open Multitask for cleanup-only or push-only follow-ups unless the user explicitly requests it
